## What They Do

Actuaries use mathematics and statistics to help companies predict financial risks, unexpected events, and future expenses. Day-to-day work involves heavy use of Microsoft Excel and some coding; they apply mathematical, statistical, and financial theory to analyse data and advise organisations on financial risk.

## Aliases (Same Job, Different Titles)

- Valuation Actuary
- Actuarial Executive
- Mathematician
- Demographer

## Career Progression & Salary (RM)

| Level | Titles | Salary Range | Typical Experience |
|-------|--------|-------------|-------------------|
| Early Career | Associate (Sekutu) | 2,800 – 7,000 | 0 years |
| Supervisory | Senior Associate | 3,500 – 9,000 | ~2 years |
| Managerial | Manager (Pengurus) | 8,000 – 19,000 | ~6 years |
| Leadership | Appointed Actuary (Aktuari Dilantik) | 30,000 – 75,000+ | ~15 years |

Salary increases with each actuarial exam passed (potentially adding up to RM 7,000 per exam). Certification unlocks the Appointed Actuary title, which carries authority over financial decisions and regulatory approvals. *(Source: Anisha Puri, Actuary, Allianz Malaysia; Jobstreet, Glassdoor, Hays Salary Guide 2024)*

## Education Pathways

Two main routes post-SPM:

| Step | Degree Pathway (4–6 yrs) | Professional Certification Pathway (7–13 yrs) |
|------|--------------------------|-----------------------------------------------|
| Pre-U | STPM / Asasi / Matriks / A-Levels / Foundation | STPM / Asasi / Matriks / A-Levels / Foundation |
| Degree | Actuarial Science (3–4 yrs) | Any degree (3–4 yrs) |
| Certification | — | Actuarial Exams IFoA/SOA (3–7 yrs) |
| Entry Title | Actuarial Associate | Certified Actuary |

An Actuarial Science degree may grant exam exemptions. Students without that degree can still qualify by passing all professional exams. *(Source: Farhana, Actuary)*

## Demand

High demand in insurance companies and consulting firms, both locally and globally. Demand increases significantly after gaining experience and certification.

